title: Texas Firm Recalls Ground Beef Products Due to Mislabeling and Possible Adulteration
summary: WASHINGTON, Dec. 17, 2010 - Winn Meats Co., a Dallas, Texas, establishment, is recalling approximately 25,600 pounds of ground beef products that were improperly labeled and potentially adulterated, the U.S. Department of Agriculture’s Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) announced today. The products’ labels include...
impacted_products: 60-pound boxes of “Ground Beef for Cooking Only”
